    "Even in this early period in his life, W\u00f6lfflin's interest focused on the principles for analyzing works of art as much as the art itself.</p>\n\n<p>The two years after his dissertation were spent in Italy, resulting in his <em>habilitationschrift</em> and first book, <em>Renaissance und Barock</em> (1888).": [
