    "W\u00f6lfflin authored his only monograph on an individual artist, <em>Die Kunst Albrecht D\u00fcrers</em> (1905) during this time, partially to appease critics that this non-German art historian was teaching in Berlin.</p>\n\n<p>He met and became engaged to Adele Auguste (\"Ada\") Bruhn (1885-1951), daughter of a wealthy factory owner and dancer.": [
