                "Bruh",
                "Bruhs"
            ]
        ]
    ],
    "The contrast of Berlin to the other universities where W\u00f6lfflin had taught, particularly the conservative climate of Imperial Prussia--and particularly Wilhelm II's antagonism for modern art and \"non-Germans\"--eventually caused W\u00f6lfflin to resign his chair in 1910, along with <em>Nationalgalerie</em> art director <a href=\"/tschudih\">Hugo von Tschudi</a>.": [
        [
