    "The anonymous review of the English edition of <em>Klassische Kunst</em> (1903) in the <em>Athenaeum</em>, written by the British art historian <a href=\"/fryr\">Roger Fry</a>, shows the enthusiasm with which his books were received.": [],
    "<a href=\"/berensonb\">Bernard Berenson</a> mused in the second edition to his <em>Drawings of the Florentine Painters</em> (1938), \"would that our studies had more W\u00f6lfflins!\"": [],
    "W\u00f6lfflin's books, in contrast to the academic art-historical tomes of the time, were short and pithy, accounting for their popularity.": [
        [
            0,
