    "His profile was so significant during his lifetime that he saw books written about his research (B\u00f6ckelmann, 1938).</p>\n\n<p>Methodology: W\u00f6lfflin began his art career by focusing on the psychology of artistic appreciation and never really strayed from this essential view.": [
